A photographer has launched an appeal to reunite a family with their lost holiday pictures taken 40 years ago, after she bought a second-hand camera with undeveloped film.

Cali Teasel, 22, found colourful images on the Ensign Selfix 16-20 camera depicting a young family enjoying a sunny day in Llanfairfechan and Llandudno, two seaside resorts in north Wales.

She had purchased the device made by British camera-maker Houghton-Butcher from Lichfield Antiques Centre in Staffordshire - which is about 150 miles away from the two beaches.

